card.description: A conservative film now playing in select theaters around the country isn't "determinative, definitive" proof of widespread voter fraud, as former President Donald Trump has claimed.
card.title: Evidence Gaps in '2000 Mules' - FactCheck.org

_source.content:
Horse Lover, I watched it. I didn't find it convincing at all. Among the issues I had with it were: the extreme speculations presented as facts, the extensive use of ominous soundtracks and black and white filters, and that the panel chosen to evaluate the claims was: Dennis Prager, Larry Elder, Sebastian Gorka, Charlie Kirk, and Eric Metaxas. WTF?

@RanmaOtherHalf gives a nice overview of issues here:

https://truthsocial.com/@RanmaOtherHalf/posts/108612554246044674

This article is more comprehensive:

https://www.factcheck.org/2022/06/evidence-gaps-in-2000-mules/
